Initializing a variable like let cost = 0 and constantly mutating it through multiple blocks of arithmetic operations introduces cognitive load and points of failure. If an unexpected condition triggers, or if a developer adds a line of code in the middle of the function later on, the state of cost can easily become corrupted.

